  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project comprises long-term working capital funding, and necessary equipment maintenance and upgrades, to help to mitigate the impact of the COVID pandemic on Kioo Limited, a glass container manufacturing business based in Dar es Salaam, Tanzania.&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;  This project is linked to&#xA0;https://disclosures.ifc.org/#/projectDetail/SII/38664</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">By supporting Kioo to sustain operations, IFC positions the private sector in Tanzania to contribute to economic recovery and improved market resilience in the regional beverages supply chain in which Kioo participates.

Development outcome indicators to be tracked for the duration of the IFC investment: employment (number of direct jobs); production volume; purchases from domestic suppliers; number of countries supplied.</narrative>
  </description>
